<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-16T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-16T02:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7056: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Legation in China</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-16T15:00:00+08:00">June 16, 1935—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>165. Shanghai’s 315, June 15, 9 a.m.<note n="83" xml:id="d211fn83">Not
                                printed.</note> Director of Department of Information and Publicity
                            of the Foreign Office has informed me that <pb facs="0367" n="255" xml:id="pg_255"/> censorship has been lifted on press despatches
                            concerning situation in North China and an American newspaper
                            correspondent from Shanghai confirms this statement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>